main event: Two observers reported sighting three disc-shaped objects in the sky over just east of Austin, Texas, on May 8, 1959.
interesting points: The objects were described as dark in color, estimated to be 40 to 60 feet in diameter., The objects were moving at a very rapid speed estimated at approximately 800 mph., The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes., Two independent observers reported consistent accounts of the sighting., The objects disappeared toward the northeast.
sighted object: three disc-shaped objects in the sky
